snippet.textDisplay: This song begins my day and ends it. I am on a spiritual discourse and hence have given up all assumptions about the existence of God. But listening to such songs, either sufi or not, make me cry. The devotional essence of a song like this reminds me the actually beautiful side of religion. Shafaqat sa'ab and Ahmed sa'ab have voices that are in perfect harmony with the crux of the song. The chorus binds a spell on you and the lyrics are beautiful. I am short on words on how I can describe the beauty of this song. No assumptions here, and no conclusions. I am spellbound, and in love. <3
